287 rlReturnVal_t rlSetMultiBpmChirpConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlUInt16_t cnt,
288  rlBpmChirpCfg_t** data)
289 {
290  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
291  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlSetMultiBpmChirpConfig starts...\n");
292 
293  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
294  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || (RL_NULL_PTR == data) || \
295  (cnt == 0U))
296  {
297  /* set return error code */
298  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
299  }
300  else
301  {
302  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
303  rlDriverMsg_t inMsg;
304  rlDriverMsg_t outMsg = {0};
305 
306  /* Index and other paramerters to send multiple sub blocks in one/more commands chunk */
307  rlUInt16_t sbLen, maxSbCntInMsg, sbCntInMsg, numChnkOfMsg, lastSbCntInMsg, loopCnt, indx;
308 
309 
310  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
311  rlPayloadSb_t inPayloadSb[RL_CMD_PL_LEN_MAX/(sizeof(rlBpmChirpCfg_t) + \
312  RL_SBC_ID_SIZE + RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE)];
313 
314  /* single sub-block length for chirp config API */
315  sbLen = (rlUInt16_t)(sizeof(rlBpmChirpCfg_t) + (RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE + RL_SBC_ID_SIZE));
316 
317  /* get Max Sub Block count */
318  /* AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:D.4.1 <APPROVED> "sbLen can not be zero" */
319  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 127 D */
320  maxSbCntInMsg = (RL_CMD_PL_LEN_MAX /sbLen);
321 
322  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_OK;
323  /* if requested count of chirpConfig is within one Message packet */
324  if (cnt <= maxSbCntInMsg)
325  {
326  sbCntInMsg = cnt;
327  numChnkOfMsg = 1U;
328  lastSbCntInMsg = 0U;
329  }
330  else
331  {
332  sbCntInMsg = maxSbCntInMsg;
333  numChnkOfMsg = cnt / maxSbCntInMsg;
334  lastSbCntInMsg = cnt % maxSbCntInMsg;
335  }
336 
337  /* Fill in-message packet */
338  rlDriverConstructInMsg(RL_RF_ADVANCED_FEATURES_SET_MSG, &inMsg, &inPayloadSb[0]);
339 
340  loopCnt = (lastSbCntInMsg == 0U) ? numChnkOfMsg : (numChnkOfMsg + 1U);
341 
342  while (retVal == RL_RET_CODE_OK)
343  {
344  /* all full messages have been sent, then send last partial message */
345  if ((loopCnt == 1U) && (lastSbCntInMsg != 0U))
346  {
347  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = lastSbCntInMsg;
348  }
349  else
350  {
351  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = sbCntInMsg;
352  }
353 
354  for (indx = 0U; indx < inMsg.opcode.nsbc; indx++)
355  {
356  /* Set Command Sub Block*/
357  /* AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.2.2 <APPROVED> "Values are used by called function. \
358  LDRA Tool Issue" */
359  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 105 D */
360  inPayloadSb[indx].sbid = RL_GET_UNIQUE_SBID(RL_RF_ADVANCED_FEATURES_SET_MSG,
361  RL_RF_BPM_CHIRP_CONF_SB);
362  /* AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.2.2 <APPROVED> "Values are used by called function. \
363  LDRA Tool Issue" */
364  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 105 D */
365  inPayloadSb[indx].len = (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlBpmChirpCfg_t);
366  /* AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.2.2 <APPROVED> "Values are used by called function. \
367  LDRA Tool Issue" */
368  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 105 D */
369  inPayloadSb[indx].pSblkData = (rlUInt8_t*)(*data);
370 
371  /*AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.18.1 <APPROVED> "require pointer increment to jump to
372  next profile Config */
373  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 567 S */
374  data++;
375  }
376  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
377  retVal += rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
378  loopCnt--;
379 
380  if (loopCnt == 0U)
381  {
382  break;
383  }
384  }
385  }
386  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlSetMultiBpmChirpConfig ends...\n");
387 
388  return retVal;
389 }

431 rlReturnVal_t rlSetProfileConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlUInt16_t cnt,
432  rlProfileCfg_t* data)
433 {
434  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
435 
436  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlSetProfileConfig starts...\n");
437 
438  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
439  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || \
440  (RL_NULL_PTR == data) || (cnt == 0U))
441  {
442  /* set return error code */
443  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
444  RL_LOGE_ARG0("rlSetProfileConfig, Invalid device map\n");
445  }
446  else
447  {
448  rlDriverMsg_t inMsg = {0};
449  rlDriverMsg_t outMsg = {0};
450 
451  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
452  rlPayloadSb_t inPayloadSb[RL_CMD_PL_LEN_MAX/(sizeof(rlProfileCfg_t) + \
453  RL_SBC_ID_SIZE + RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE)];
454  /* Variable to count message chunks */
455  rlUInt16_t indx;
456  rlUInt16_t sbCntInAllChunk = 0U;
457  rlUInt16_t maxSbInMsg = (RL_CMD_PL_LEN_MAX /(sizeof(rlProfileCfg_t) + \
458  RL_SBC_ID_SIZE + RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE));
459 
460  /* Construct command packet */
461  rlDriverConstructInMsg(RL_RF_DYNAMIC_CONF_SET_MSG, &inMsg, &inPayloadSb[0]);
462 
463  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_OK;
464  /* Loop to copy all the command data to one message */
465  for (indx = 0U; (indx < cnt) && (retVal == RL_RET_CODE_OK); indx++)
466  {
467  /* Fill in-message payload */
468  /*AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.18.1 <APPROVED> "require pointer increment to jump to
469  next profile Config */
470  /*AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:R.18.4 <APPROVED> "require pointer increment to jump to
471  next profile Config */
472  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 87 S */
473  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 567 S */
474  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_DYNAMIC_CONF_SET_MSG, RL_RF_PROFILE_CONF_SB,
475  &inPayloadSb[indx], (rlUInt8_t*)(data + indx),
476  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlProfileCfg_t));
477 
478  /* increment Sub-block count in one packet */
479  sbCntInAllChunk++;
480 
481  /* check if total payload length is going beyond defined limitation */
482  if ((maxSbInMsg == (indx + 1U)) || (cnt == sbCntInAllChunk))
483  {
484  /* setting of numSBC to inMsg */
485  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = (indx + 1U);
486  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
487  retVal += rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
488  }
489  }
490  }
491 
492  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlSetProfileConfig ends...\n");
493 
494  return retVal;
495 }

517 rlReturnVal_t rlGetProfileConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlUInt16_t profileId, rlProfileCfg_t* data)
518 {
519  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
520 
521  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlGetProfileConfig ends...\n");
522 
523  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
524  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || \
525  (RL_NULL_PTR == data))
526  {
527  /* set return error code */
528  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
529  RL_LOGE_ARG0("rlGetProfileConfig, Invalid device map\n");
530  }
531  else
532  {
533  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
534  rlDriverMsg_t inMsg = {0};
535  rlDriverMsg_t outMsg = {0};
536  rlPayloadSb_t inPayloadSb = {0};
537  rlPayloadSb_t outPayloadSb = {0};
538  rlWordParam_t wordParam;
539  /* combine half words into WORD structure */
540  wordParam.halfWordOne = profileId;
541  wordParam.halfWordTwo = 0U;
542 
543  /* Construct command packet */
544  rlDriverConstructInMsg(RL_RF_DYNAMIC_CONF_GET_MSG, &inMsg, &inPayloadSb);
545  /* Fill in-message Payload */
546  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_DYNAMIC_CONF_GET_MSG, RL_RF_PROFILE_CONF_SB, &inPayloadSb,
547  (rlUInt8_t*)&wordParam, (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlWordParam_t));
548 
549  /* Construct response packet */
550  rlDriverConstructOutMsg(1U, &outMsg, &outPayloadSb);
551  /* Fill in-message Payload */
552  rlDriverFillPayload(0U, 0U, &outPayloadSb, (rlUInt8_t*)data, 0U);
553 
554  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
555  retVal = rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
556  }
557 
558  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlGetProfileConfig ends...\n");
559  return retVal;
560 }

1981  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */

1984  /* Index and other paramerters to send multiple sub blocks in one/more commands chunk */
1985  rlUInt16_t sbLen, maxSbCntInMsg, sbCntInMsg, numChnkOfMsg, lastSbCntInMsg, loopCnt, indx;
1986

1989  RL_SBC_ID_SIZE + RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE)];

1992  sbLen = (rlUInt16_t)(sizeof(rlRfPhaseShiftCfg_t) + (RL_SBC_LEN_SIZE + RL_SBC_ID_SIZE));

1995  /* AR_CODE_REVIEW MR:D.4.1 <APPROVED> "sbLen can not be zero" */

2001  if (cnt <= maxSbCntInMsg)

2005  lastSbCntInMsg = 0U;

2011  lastSbCntInMsg = cnt % maxSbCntInMsg;

2016  /* get the loop count in form of number of msg chunks */

2018

2026  else

2048  next chirp Config */
2049  /*LDRA_INSPECTED 567 S */
2050  data++;
